---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Us — TheFilamentCalc"
  description="Learn about TheFilamentCalc — a free, browser-based 3D printer filament calculator built for makers, hobbyists, and print farms."
  canonical="https://thefilamentcalc.com/about"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-eyebrow">About</div>
      <h1 class="page-title">Built for 3D printing makers.</h1>
      <p class="page-lead">
        TheFilamentCalc is a free, privacy-first utility that runs entirely in your browser.
        No accounts, no tracking, no server calls — just fast, accurate filament math.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-body">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Why we built this</h2>
      <p>
        Every 3D printing slicer reports material usage in grams, but spools are sold by weight
        and priced per kilogram. Converting between the two — accounting for material density,
        filament diameter, and spool cost — requires math that most makers do on a napkin or
        in a spreadsheet. We built TheFilamentCalc to make that instant.
      </p>

      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <p>
        The calculator uses the volumetric density of each polymer (PLA, ABS, PETG, TPU) and
        the cross-sectional geometry of 1.75mm filament to compute exact length from weight.
        All arithmetic runs client-side in vanilla JavaScript — no frameworks, no APIs.
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        We do not collect any personal data. Your recent weight entries are stored only in your
        own browser's <code>localStorage</code> and never leave your device.
        See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for full details.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: 80px 0 48px;
    background: var(--bg);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .page-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--fg-mute);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -1.5px;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .page-lead {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 27px;
    color: var(--fg-body);
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .page-body {
    padding: 56px 0 80px;
    background: var(--bg-soft);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.6px;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 32px 0 10px;
  }

  .prose p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 26px;
    color: var(--fg-body);
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .prose code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--bg-soft2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-link, #0070f3);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
